==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: bonobo
<hw>bo*no"bo</hw> <pr>(b⟦osl⟧*n⟦omac⟧"b⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>An anthropoid ape (<spn>Pan paniscus</spn>), resembling but smaller
than the common chimpanzee (<spn>Pan troglodytes</spn>); -- called also
<altname>pygmy chimpanzee</altname>. It is found in the forests of
Zaire. Its genome is the closest known to humans, differing by less than
2% in nucleotide sequence.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pygmy chimpanzee, pygmy chimp.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bon Silene</ent>⟦br⟧
